WEBVTT

00:02.089 --> 00:03.481
♪ Hey, here's comes Sunny,
keeping it fun ♪

00:03.612 --> 00:05.135
♪ Never says never,
never gives up ♪

00:05.266 --> 00:06.441
♪ It's Sunny!

00:06.571 --> 00:09.096
♪ Yeah, she's Sunny! Hey!

00:09.226 --> 00:11.359
♪ Gear up and go
in the Glam Van ♪

00:11.489 --> 00:12.969
♪ Hairstylin'
with her best friends ♪

00:13.100 --> 00:14.362
♪ It's Sunny

00:14.492 --> 00:15.754
♪ Yeah, she's Sunny

00:15.885 --> 00:19.280
♪ Oh, it's a Sunny day

00:19.410 --> 00:23.153
♪ She'll put a smile
on your face ♪

00:23.284 --> 00:28.028
♪ Sunny is shining
all the way ♪

00:28.158 --> 00:31.074
♪ Yeah, she's Sunny,
yeah, she's Sunny ♪

00:31.205 --> 00:32.989
♪ Having a sunny Sunny day! ♪

00:33.120 --> 00:34.860
Yeah!Whoo-hoo!

00:40.040 --> 00:42.955
♪♪

00:45.567 --> 00:46.916
Hmm.

00:50.180 --> 00:53.227
[hair dryer running]

00:53.357 --> 00:56.665
There! Clean and clear
and ready for gear.

00:56.795 --> 00:58.884
Ooh, I love it
when the salon

00:59.015 --> 01:01.104
gets new hair supplies.

01:02.975 --> 01:04.281
I can't wait to try

01:04.412 --> 01:05.500
all the different stuff
that came in.

01:05.630 --> 01:06.805
[laughing]

01:06.936 --> 01:08.242
Once we figure out...
[groaning]

01:08.372 --> 01:10.200
where to put it all.

01:10.331 --> 01:13.203
That's my favorite part.
Mmm! [sighs]

01:13.334 --> 01:16.119
Cleaning, sorting,
alphabetizing.

01:16.250 --> 01:18.165
Best day ever!

01:20.384 --> 01:21.907
♪ Whoa, yeah yeah

01:22.038 --> 01:25.302
♪ I'm dusting the floor
with my paws, yeah ♪

01:25.433 --> 01:28.653
[laughing]
Looks like Doodle
agrees with you.

01:28.784 --> 01:31.395
What?
Noodle cheese for two?

01:31.526 --> 01:34.224
No, thanks.
I'm not hungry.

01:34.355 --> 01:35.834
[laughing]

01:35.965 --> 01:39.055
Oh, look!
My new bendy curlers!

01:39.186 --> 01:42.624
They can twist hair into any
shape you can think of. See?

01:42.754 --> 01:44.147
Cool!Nice!

01:44.278 --> 01:46.584
[laughing]
This is so much fun!

01:46.715 --> 01:48.456
Here's my new hat.

01:48.586 --> 01:51.023
I love it even more
than in the pictures!

01:51.154 --> 01:52.242
[groaning][gasps]

01:52.373 --> 01:56.290
[groaning]

01:56.420 --> 01:58.161
Whew!
This one is heavy!

01:58.292 --> 02:00.250
Arrggh!
[screams]

02:00.381 --> 02:01.686
[giggling]

02:01.817 --> 02:04.559
Um, did anyone order
a little brother?

02:04.689 --> 02:06.300
[laughing]
Hey!
I'm a pirate,

02:06.430 --> 02:07.518
not a little brother.

02:07.649 --> 02:09.825
[gasps]
Sing another? Okay.

02:09.955 --> 02:13.220
♪ La la la la la mmm

02:13.350 --> 02:15.744
♪ Oh yeah Oh!

02:15.874 --> 02:19.139
The floor is the ocean
and this is my boat. See?

02:20.531 --> 02:22.446
Junior,
we're trying to tidy,

02:22.577 --> 02:23.882
not sail the ocean.

02:24.013 --> 02:26.624
Iceberg!
Abandon ship!
[gasps]

02:28.148 --> 02:29.584
Arrggh!
Hey!

02:29.714 --> 02:31.412
I brought you to the salon
today to help us,

02:31.542 --> 02:33.414
not to play--
remember?

02:33.544 --> 02:37.200
I know, but sorting
nail polish is boring.

02:37.331 --> 02:40.986
Color coordinating
is never boring.

02:43.859 --> 02:46.601
Red and another red.

02:46.731 --> 02:49.256
They're all
just red. See?

02:49.386 --> 02:51.606
Actually,
that one's strawberry

02:51.736 --> 02:54.783
and that one's
clearly cranberry.

02:54.913 --> 02:56.567
Hey, Junior,
how'd you like to join

02:56.698 --> 02:58.613
our trash hockey team?

03:00.919 --> 03:02.094
Cool!

03:02.225 --> 03:03.313
Every time you get
a piece of trash

03:03.444 --> 03:04.967
in the can,
you score a goal.

03:05.097 --> 03:06.664
I want to try!

03:08.405 --> 03:10.102
Just three seconds
on the clock.

03:10.233 --> 03:12.235
It's up to Junior
to win the game.

03:12.366 --> 03:13.671
Will he do it?

03:16.457 --> 03:18.807
Yes!
The crowd goes wild!

03:18.937 --> 03:20.374
Yeah!Yeah!

03:20.504 --> 03:22.637
Teddy, did you see that?

03:22.767 --> 03:24.769
Oh! Teddy?

03:24.900 --> 03:27.598
[gasps]
Oh, no! He's gone!

03:27.729 --> 03:30.427
Teddy?
Teddy?

03:30.558 --> 03:32.386
Um, who's Teddy?

03:32.516 --> 03:33.952
Junior's toy bear.

03:34.083 --> 03:36.564
He never goes anywhere
without him.

03:36.694 --> 03:39.001
Teddy?!
He's not here.

03:39.131 --> 03:40.437
He's not anywhere.

03:40.568 --> 03:42.222
Are you okay, Junior?

03:42.352 --> 03:44.485
Sure. Yeah.

03:44.615 --> 03:49.490
I mean, he's just a toy
that I've have forever.

03:49.620 --> 03:52.710
Don't worry, Junior.
We'll help you find Teddy.

03:52.841 --> 03:57.019
Hey! I bet he went back
to his favorite place.

03:57.149 --> 03:59.848
We were just there today.
Come on, follow me!

03:59.978 --> 04:03.373
Oh, okay. Wait for us
at the Glam Van.

04:03.504 --> 04:05.680
Ready...Set...

04:05.810 --> 04:08.117
[all]
Gear up and go!

04:08.248 --> 04:09.814
♪♪

04:09.945 --> 04:11.860
Bye, Doodle!
We'll be back soon!

04:11.990 --> 04:14.645
Why would I want to see
a baboon?

04:14.776 --> 04:17.387
[humming]

04:17.518 --> 04:19.433
Whoops! Whoa!

04:19.563 --> 04:23.698
Whoa! A teddy bear?

04:23.828 --> 04:25.830
Friendly looking guy.

04:25.961 --> 04:28.833
Where did you come from?

04:28.964 --> 04:30.487
[gasps]

04:30.618 --> 04:33.621
Sunny must have
ordered it for me.

04:33.751 --> 04:35.710
[gasps]
She's the best!

04:35.840 --> 04:38.669
Let's see if you
pass the hug test.

04:38.800 --> 04:43.370
Mmm! Yeah! Mm-hmm!
Hug test passed.

04:43.500 --> 04:45.589
Soft, cuddly, adorable...

04:45.720 --> 04:47.069
You're perfect!

04:47.199 --> 04:51.247
I'm gonna call you
Sir Bearlington.

04:51.378 --> 04:52.814
Yay!

04:52.944 --> 04:54.468
Come on, Sir Bearlington.

04:54.598 --> 04:58.298
I'll give you a tour
of the salon.

04:58.428 --> 05:01.431
Over here is where I chased
my tail for the first time

05:01.562 --> 05:04.478
and caught it,
proud to say.

05:06.131 --> 05:08.699
Oh, and here's where Sunny
likes to groom me.

05:08.830 --> 05:10.614
You have to try out
the chair.

05:10.745 --> 05:12.747
[laughing]

05:15.315 --> 05:16.577
Turn here!

05:17.665 --> 05:19.319
Oh!
Whoa!

05:19.449 --> 05:22.800
Junior, give us a little
more warning next time.

05:22.931 --> 05:24.715
Okay. Stop now!

05:24.846 --> 05:27.327
[brakes screeching]

05:27.457 --> 05:29.807
You think Teddy might be
at Cindy's bakery?

05:29.938 --> 05:31.896
This place has
Teddy's favorite cookies.

05:32.027 --> 05:34.159
I bet he came here
to get one.

05:34.290 --> 05:36.161
Can teddy bears eat?

05:36.292 --> 05:38.642
Junior has
a big imagination,

05:38.773 --> 05:40.470
but he might have
brought Teddy here

05:40.601 --> 05:42.646
and left him behind
accidentally.

05:42.777 --> 05:45.475
If he did, maybe
Cindy found him.

05:45.606 --> 05:47.869
We'll never know
'til we give it a go.

05:47.999 --> 05:50.611
[dinging]Oh! Be right
with you! Oh!

05:50.741 --> 05:53.657
Oh... Oh!
[coughs]

05:53.788 --> 05:55.180
[clears throat]

05:55.311 --> 05:57.748
Whoa!
[groaning]

05:57.879 --> 06:00.360
Hello? Is there
someone there?

06:00.490 --> 06:02.274
Hi, Cindy.
It's me, Junior.

06:03.667 --> 06:05.495
Hi, Junior.

06:05.626 --> 06:07.497
Did you change
your hair?

06:07.628 --> 06:08.977
[laughing]

06:09.107 --> 06:11.240
That would be
a cake.

06:11.371 --> 06:13.242
Can I borrow your glasses
for a second?

06:15.331 --> 06:18.160
[hair dryer running]

06:19.248 --> 06:20.684
Oh!
[laughing]

06:20.815 --> 06:21.990
Thanks, Sunny.

06:22.120 --> 06:24.819
I dropped my glasses
in the bag of flour.

06:24.949 --> 06:27.604
Cindy, did Teddy come here
to get a cookie?

06:27.735 --> 06:31.086
No. He hasn't been in
without you.

06:31.216 --> 06:32.522
Teddy's missing.

06:32.653 --> 06:34.959
Junior thought we
might find him here.

06:35.090 --> 06:37.397
Oh, I'm sorry, Junior.

06:37.527 --> 06:40.791
The only fluffy,
fuzzy thing here is Ralph.

06:40.922 --> 06:42.097
[Ralph meows]

06:42.227 --> 06:44.360
I wish I could
help you.

06:44.491 --> 06:47.581
Maybe a cookie
will cheer you up?

06:47.711 --> 06:48.538
[Ralph meows]

06:48.669 --> 06:50.105
No, thanks.

06:50.235 --> 06:52.412
It just won't taste
the same without Teddy.

06:52.542 --> 06:53.848
[sighs]

06:55.937 --> 06:56.981
[gasps]

06:57.112 --> 06:58.809
Teddy?

06:58.940 --> 07:00.550
Teddy!Junior!

07:02.683 --> 07:05.033
Can you make
that cookie to go?

07:05.163 --> 07:06.469
Come on, Rox.Whoa!

07:06.600 --> 07:08.558
Bye, Cindy!
Have a Sunny day!

07:08.689 --> 07:09.864
Bye, guys!

07:11.779 --> 07:13.737
Teddy!

07:13.868 --> 07:14.738
Teddy!

07:14.869 --> 07:16.566
Whoa! Aah!

07:16.697 --> 07:18.350
It's just Scratch.

07:18.481 --> 07:19.700
Why are you
dressed like that?

07:19.830 --> 07:21.484
[gasps]
Did I forget Halloween?

07:21.615 --> 07:23.791
[laughing]
Um, no.

07:23.921 --> 07:26.750
This is my clever disguise.

07:26.881 --> 07:29.536
See, I figure
if I look like a dog...

07:29.666 --> 07:30.667
You'll catch fleas?

07:30.798 --> 07:33.540
No.
I'll find other dogs.

07:33.670 --> 07:35.063
It takes one to catch one,
you know,

07:35.193 --> 07:37.544
and I'm always on the lookout
for lost dogs.

07:37.674 --> 07:39.328
Then maybe
you can help us?

07:39.459 --> 07:41.286
We're trying to find
a lost teddy.

07:41.417 --> 07:44.202
What kind of dog is Teddy?

07:44.333 --> 07:46.030
A bear.
Aah! A bear?

07:46.161 --> 07:48.555
Where?
Save yourselves!

07:49.860 --> 07:50.818
Car.

07:53.734 --> 07:55.649
Scratch, it's okay.

07:55.779 --> 07:57.215
Teddy is a teddy bear.

07:57.346 --> 08:00.044
Ah! Well, I only
look for dogs.

08:00.175 --> 08:03.570
It's what I do best.

08:03.700 --> 08:06.964
But I will keep
an eye out for your teddy,

08:07.095 --> 08:08.488
just in case.

08:08.618 --> 08:11.186
[sighs]
Thanks.

08:11.316 --> 08:12.448
Junior?

08:12.579 --> 08:13.667
Bye, Scratch.

08:13.797 --> 08:15.451
See ya!Goodbye!

08:15.582 --> 08:17.453
Bye!
Oops.

08:17.584 --> 08:20.891
[straining]

08:21.022 --> 08:24.242
Um, a little help?
Hello?

08:26.114 --> 08:27.115
[sniffling]

08:27.245 --> 08:28.986
Uh, you okay?

08:29.117 --> 08:31.119
I really miss Teddy.

08:31.249 --> 08:34.426
Oh, this feels like
a group hug moment.

08:34.557 --> 08:35.471
[both laughing]

08:35.602 --> 08:36.951
Um, thanks, Blair.

08:37.081 --> 08:38.474
[groans]Heh!

08:38.605 --> 08:41.521
Junior, don't be sad.
We'll find him.

08:41.651 --> 08:43.610
How? He could be
anywhere.

08:43.740 --> 08:47.570
Oh, what if he's
gone... forever?

08:51.443 --> 08:52.880
[sighs]

08:53.010 --> 08:55.186
We'll never find Teddy.

08:55.317 --> 08:56.623
Never say never.

08:56.753 --> 08:58.146
We just have to
keep looking.

08:58.276 --> 09:00.496
Yeah!Yes!

09:00.627 --> 09:03.107
And Scratch
gave me an idea.

09:03.238 --> 09:06.502
If he dresses like
a dog to find a dog,

09:06.633 --> 09:10.071
then maybe we need to be
bears to find a bear.

09:11.246 --> 09:12.203
[beeps]

09:16.860 --> 09:18.993
Time for some bear hair.

09:19.123 --> 09:20.951
Rox, you first.

09:22.605 --> 09:25.826
I'm just going to
part your hair and...

09:29.264 --> 09:31.135
There.
That should do it.

09:31.266 --> 09:33.442
And the other side.

09:37.402 --> 09:40.101
Some hairpins...
and done!

09:40.231 --> 09:42.973
Yes! Your turn, Blair.

09:48.283 --> 09:50.198
Well, Junior,
what do you think?

09:50.328 --> 09:52.722
[gasps]
Wow!

09:52.853 --> 09:54.550
We're The Three Bears!

09:54.681 --> 09:57.335
And we're just right.

09:57.466 --> 09:58.423
[laughing]

09:58.554 --> 09:59.860
Hold still,
everybody.

09:59.990 --> 10:03.254
Hang on. I want to
put the hat on.

10:03.385 --> 10:05.779
It's my new favorite
thing in the world.

10:05.909 --> 10:06.867
[camera shutter snaps]

10:06.997 --> 10:08.042
[Sunny laughs]

10:08.172 --> 10:09.739
That's one
for the Style Files.

10:09.870 --> 10:11.045
[laughing]

10:11.175 --> 10:12.612
Teddy, you've got to
check this out.

10:12.742 --> 10:13.830
You've got to see...

10:13.961 --> 10:16.920
Oh, I forgot.
He's not here.

10:17.051 --> 10:18.574
Don't worry, Junior.

10:18.705 --> 10:20.358
We'll keep
looking for him.

10:20.489 --> 10:22.447
Let's retrace
your steps.

10:22.578 --> 10:24.841
Where did you go
with Teddy this morning?

10:24.972 --> 10:28.105
Well... I took him
to the playground!

10:28.236 --> 10:29.498
Let's look there!

10:30.804 --> 10:35.983
Teddy! Teddy!
Where are you?

10:36.113 --> 10:38.289
Hmm. Keep looking,
everyone.

10:41.336 --> 10:43.425
[gasps]
Teddy loves coming here!

10:43.555 --> 10:46.297
Look! Here's the first
slide we ever slid.

10:46.428 --> 10:49.083
Wow. That's
pretty tall.

10:49.213 --> 10:50.824
Yeah. Teddy was
scared at first,

10:50.954 --> 10:52.608
but I held his hand.

10:52.739 --> 10:56.351
I guess I'll have to ride it
on my own from now on.

10:56.481 --> 10:59.571
Not today. Let's all go
down the slide together.

10:59.702 --> 11:01.965
Come on!Whoo-hoo!
Yeah!

11:05.795 --> 11:07.318
Whoo-hoo!Yeah!

11:07.449 --> 11:08.972
[laughing]

11:09.103 --> 11:11.409
Whoa!
[laughing]

11:11.540 --> 11:15.849
Oh! Whoa! Ah!
I almost lost my hat.

11:15.979 --> 11:18.373
Doesn't look like
Teddy's at the playground.

11:18.503 --> 11:20.114
Where next, Junior?

11:20.244 --> 11:21.637
Hmm...

11:21.768 --> 11:22.899
Remember,
we have to go

11:23.030 --> 11:25.685
exactly where you've
been with Teddy.

11:25.815 --> 11:27.382
Um...
[gasps]

11:27.512 --> 11:29.863
We played pirates.
This way!

11:29.993 --> 11:33.736
Oh! Junior never just
walks anywhere, does he?

11:35.912 --> 11:36.870
Uhh!

11:39.568 --> 11:41.091
Avast, ye matey!

11:41.222 --> 11:44.181
We're looking for Teddy
of the High Seas.

11:44.312 --> 11:45.705
Aye-aye, Captain Sunny.

11:45.835 --> 11:50.971
Aye! And other things
pirates say. Arrggh!

11:51.101 --> 11:53.843
Now let's go find
First Mate Teddy!

11:57.238 --> 11:59.370
Teddy!

11:59.501 --> 12:01.459
Oh. Aha! Oh.

12:01.590 --> 12:04.158
Teddy!

12:15.691 --> 12:17.780
Teddy?
Is that you?

12:17.911 --> 12:21.044
Here, doggy, doggy!
[gasps]

12:23.743 --> 12:24.744
Aah!

12:24.874 --> 12:26.397
Three bears!

12:26.528 --> 12:28.617
[laughing]

12:28.748 --> 12:31.446
Your bear hair
is really good.

12:31.576 --> 12:35.624
Maybe a little too good.
Poor Scratch.
Aah!

12:35.755 --> 12:38.758
Bears!

12:40.150 --> 12:41.978
Whenever Teddy and I
play pirates,

12:42.109 --> 12:43.763
we cross the stream
right here.

12:43.893 --> 12:45.416
That's what we did
this morning.

12:45.547 --> 12:49.246
Of course! And at the
muddiest, squishiest part!

12:49.377 --> 12:53.642
All right.
I'll do it for Junior.

12:55.862 --> 12:58.908
Blair,
what are you doing?

12:59.039 --> 13:00.344
Crossing the stream.

13:00.475 --> 13:01.824
We're supposed to do
everything

13:01.955 --> 13:05.132
exactly like Junior
and Teddy did, right?

13:05.262 --> 13:08.265
Um, we used the stones.

13:08.396 --> 13:09.963
[grunting]

13:10.093 --> 13:12.313
Whoa.
[grunts]

13:12.443 --> 13:14.271
Here, let me help you.

13:14.402 --> 13:16.665
Uhh!
[sighs]

13:16.796 --> 13:19.407
Oh! Usually when
I soak my feet,

13:19.537 --> 13:21.148
it's for a pedicure.

13:24.716 --> 13:29.156
And that's the story
of how I met Sunny.

13:29.286 --> 13:31.288
I know, right?

13:31.419 --> 13:33.029
It's a lot to take in.

13:33.160 --> 13:35.075
Hey, are you
gonna eat that?

13:37.338 --> 13:38.208
Thanks!

13:38.339 --> 13:41.298
[chomping]

13:41.429 --> 13:43.648
I feel like I can
tell you anything,

13:43.779 --> 13:45.215
Sir Bearlington.

13:45.346 --> 13:46.434
Mmm! Aw!

13:46.564 --> 13:48.262
I can't wait
to tell Sunny

13:48.392 --> 13:51.091
how glad I am
she got you for me.

13:53.528 --> 13:54.877
Arrggh!Arrggh!

13:55.008 --> 13:56.661
Arrggh!Arrggh!

13:56.792 --> 13:58.750
Huh?What's wrong, Junior?

13:58.881 --> 14:00.535
I never go any
farther than this.

14:00.665 --> 14:02.015
Why?

14:02.145 --> 14:06.802
Teddy thinks it's too
dark in those bushes.

14:06.933 --> 14:08.978
Then let's start looking
someplace else.

14:09.109 --> 14:10.632
There is no place else.

14:10.762 --> 14:12.895
We didn't go
anywhere else today.

14:13.026 --> 14:16.638
I've just got to face it.
Teddy's gone for good.

14:16.768 --> 14:18.814
Oh!

14:18.945 --> 14:22.383
Don't be sad, Junior.

14:22.513 --> 14:24.124
I'm sure gonna miss him.

14:24.254 --> 14:25.647
[sighs]

14:25.777 --> 14:29.651
Junior, what made Teddy
so special to you?

14:29.781 --> 14:33.263
I never
really thought about it.

14:33.394 --> 14:35.091
♪ What can I say
about Teddy? ♪

14:35.222 --> 14:38.225
♪ Well let me see

14:38.355 --> 14:43.404
♪ He likes so many of
the very same things as me ♪

14:43.534 --> 14:47.799
♪ He makes me laugh
and I want you all to know ♪

14:47.930 --> 14:53.936
♪ I love him so,
I love him so ♪

14:54.067 --> 14:57.374
♪ Teddy likes going on
adventures the way I do ♪

14:57.505 --> 14:59.159
♪♪[gasps]

14:59.289 --> 15:03.815
♪ He's soft and fluffy
and brave and bold and true ♪

15:03.946 --> 15:08.124
♪ He's my very best friend
and that's why you should know ♪

15:08.255 --> 15:13.608
♪ I love him so,
I love him so ♪

15:13.738 --> 15:18.656
♪ And how my heart,
it fills with pride ♪

15:18.787 --> 15:24.227
♪ 'Cause I have Teddy
by my side ♪

15:24.358 --> 15:26.838
♪ Wherever I go

