15:36.500 --> 15:39.286
Here.
I know it's not Teddy,

15:39.416 --> 15:42.332
but this guy
love adventures too.

15:42.463 --> 15:44.682
I'm sure he wants to
hear your stories

15:44.813 --> 15:46.771
and he could
really use a friend.

15:46.902 --> 15:48.599
Think you could
give him a try?

15:50.384 --> 15:52.212
[gasps]
My hat!

15:54.518 --> 15:55.737
Aah!

15:59.088 --> 15:59.959
[groaning]

16:00.089 --> 16:01.525
I can't reach.

16:01.656 --> 16:02.700
[groans]

16:02.831 --> 16:05.442
The best hat
in the world

16:05.573 --> 16:08.968
and I didn't even get to
wear it for the whole day.

16:09.098 --> 16:11.274
Oh! First Teddy
disappears

16:11.405 --> 16:13.015
and now you lose
your hat.

16:13.146 --> 16:16.845
This day is
a complete disaster.

16:20.066 --> 16:21.328
[straining]

16:21.458 --> 16:22.807
It's no use!

16:22.938 --> 16:24.679
[straining]

16:24.809 --> 16:27.160
If only my arms
were longer.

16:27.290 --> 16:28.813
Or the bushes
were shorter.

16:28.944 --> 16:32.426
Maybe I can help.
Some ribbon,

16:32.556 --> 16:34.515
a hair clip...

16:36.778 --> 16:39.128
Done.
Uhh!

16:40.651 --> 16:43.263
[groans]

16:43.393 --> 16:47.571
I only have to
get it right once.

16:47.702 --> 16:50.096
I bet I can fit
through those bushes.

16:50.226 --> 16:53.360
Ooh. It's awfully
dark in there.

16:53.490 --> 16:55.101
I know you're not Teddy,

16:55.231 --> 16:58.060
but do you want to come
with me?

16:59.757 --> 17:01.107
[sighs]

17:01.237 --> 17:02.630
There has to be
some other way

17:02.760 --> 17:03.892
to get your hat
out of there.

17:04.023 --> 17:08.114
There is!
The Junior way!

17:11.421 --> 17:13.641
Junior, be careful![Junior straining]

17:13.771 --> 17:16.078
I love my hat,
but I love you more!

17:16.209 --> 17:20.169
[Junior straining]

17:20.300 --> 17:22.911
Junior, are you okay?

17:23.042 --> 17:25.348
[Junior straining]

17:25.479 --> 17:27.611
Arrggh!

17:27.742 --> 17:29.570
We got it!

17:29.700 --> 17:32.268
Yay!
Good job!
Way to go!

17:32.399 --> 17:34.749
Thanks, Junior.

17:34.879 --> 17:37.578
You looked so sad,
like how I felt

17:37.708 --> 17:38.840
when I lost Teddy.

17:38.970 --> 17:40.842
You tried to help me
get him back,

17:40.972 --> 17:42.713
so I wanted to help you.

17:42.844 --> 17:44.150
So did Roarfang.

17:44.280 --> 17:45.803
Who's Roarfang?

17:45.934 --> 17:48.284
My new toy
that Sunny made me.

17:48.415 --> 17:50.895
Oh! Does that mean
you're keeping him?

17:51.026 --> 17:53.594
You bet!
He's not afraid of the dark

17:53.724 --> 17:56.075
and his arms are great
at holding onto things.

17:56.205 --> 17:59.687
Well, thank you
and Roarfang

17:59.817 --> 18:01.689
for getting my hat.

18:01.819 --> 18:04.692
I'll still miss Teddy
and I'll never forget him,

18:04.822 --> 18:07.956
but now I have Roarfang
to go on adventures with.

18:08.087 --> 18:09.653
I think Teddy
would like that.

18:09.784 --> 18:10.959
Sorry to interrupt,

18:11.090 --> 18:12.830
